inn1.comm: lovely start for Lee. Full, fast, inswinging onto off stump. Joyce defends cagily to point
good length on off stump, hint of drift back into the batsman, pushed into the covers off the front foot
good start from Plunkett, zippy again, and a thick edge down to third man. Hayden off the mark
tight on off stump, defended back down the pitch. Tidy stuff from Plunkett, who served up an 11-ball over against New Zealand the other night
oops, it couldn't last. A swing and a miss, and the first extra. A bit harsh, to be honest
firm drive back down the ground. Too straight, and the stumps at the non-striker's end do the fielding
good first over. That was a bit straighter, and nudged into the leg-side
cracking shot. Too full and wide from Mahmood, and Hayden climbed into that - a juicy half-volley scuds through the covers
better length. That one zips through
good line now. Hayden, with his runs already in the bag, now enjoys a few sighters
steady stuff now from Mahmood, just outside off stump, Nixon takes with a flourish
tighter to the stumps, Hayden square-drives but without much power and point tidies up
and that's a carbon copy of the first ball. Full, wide, thwacked. This was more of a caress, if we are splitting hairs, but the outfield is so quick
drops a touch short, and pinged off the hip and over square leg. Just helped off the hip and fielded on the boundary
wicket-to-wicket, turned to midwicket
a fraction shorter, but too straight to work with for Hayden, and that's played straight to point
better ball. A stifled appeal as Hayden is squared up, but the ball was always going over
fantastic strike! It's that cover-drive again, for the third time in 11 balls, and this time it's Plunkett who's bowling too full and wide
poor bowling. Over-compensates with the length, bangs it in too short, and that's thumped through the covers off the back foot
Collingwood at short-extra fears for his life then, but another fierce drive eludes him
fuller and tighter to off stump. Defended
oh dear. That's not very clever. A slower ball, and it's straight down leg
back on a good length, defended
bouncer. Too short to be a danger, and a wide is called after an improbable delay from the square leg umpire
drawn forward, looking to attack, steered out to point instead
width, but not enough to work with. Cleaned up in the covers
slower ball, better line and a good full length
fended into the leg-side
speared into the pads again. Clipped fine, but not timed
on the drive again, can't beat the field
short and swivelled off the hips down to fine leg. Lucky to get away with that, as it was a bit of a long-hop again
fuller and better
a good finish to the over. Outside off stump but not by much. No room to swing the arms into a big drive
pushed out to point, beats the field
a touch short but pretty straight. A neat dab to third man

GOT HIM! And that's a big breakthrough. It was full and in Gilchrist's slot, but a touch slower, and a big swipe came straight off the toe of the bat, for Andrew Flintoff to circle beneath in the covers and take a comfortable catch. Vital wicket for England!
ooh, chancy! Looking to turn to leg, got a leading edge, and looped just short of cover! Lucky ...
pushed into the leg-side, forward to meet that one
clattered! Two sighters and now the big yahoo through the covers! That scorched to the rope. Ponting is on a mission already, one senses
good length, defended back to the bowler
a bit of a waft outside off this time from Hayden. Tried to dab it down to third man, but didn't make contact
straighter and fuller, deflected into the leg-side off the front foot
played through midwicket with soft hands
drawn forward, defended not quite off the middle of the bat. Rolls into the leg-side
deep backward-square gets down well to save two, as Hayden clips firmly again
you can' t bowl there to Ponting - a leg-stump half-volley is sent whistling through midwicket. Panesar at deep backward square covers great ground to save the boundary
slower ball, well bowled this time, and short extra tidies up
another slower delivery, misdirected this time, and turned fine
carved down to third man. Too much width this time
tighter, and defended off the front foot
width, and that is a brilliant stop from Ian Bell in the covers. Ponting absolutely drilled that, but Bell got down quickly to his right. Good work
full but slightly leg-sided. Picked up at midwicket
fuller and maybe even a hint of late swing. Either way, short cover picks up and threatens a shy at the non-striker's end
Ponting was looking to clobber that, but adjusted late and worked across the line into the leg side
another wide, another one sprayed down the leg side
a bit of an appeal from Plunkett. Pitched in line, hit in line, and Hayden was late on it, but no-one was entirely convinced. It was going over, says Hawkeye
wider and left alone with a big flourish
decent over, bar the wide. This one is fuller and straighter, and defended into the covers
full face of the bat, tidied up by the bowler
back of a length, a quick single to gully to bring up the fifty
shovelled into the covers. Not really timed, but it is a deep and fast outfield
drawn forward in a smothering defensive stroke. Played that almost like a spinner
tight lines again, defended again. Australia have made a good start, but England's bowlers haven't completely surrendered the initiative
run down to third man to complete the first powerplay
pushed into the covers again and a loud squawk as a run is turned down
big stride outside off stump, driven without power to cover
a false shot from Ponting, looking to club through the covers but instead hit all across it and out to midwicket. That was airborne for a while, but wide of the fielder
good wheels from Plunkett. That was timed at 90.5mph (145kph), which is unusally sharp. Fielded in the covers, incidentally
driven on the walk as Hayden comes out to meet the ball. One more down to long-off
beautiful shot, just caressed on the up, all the way along the ground and past deep point. Picks the gap perfectly!
typically tidy start, on off stump and defended with a big stride
untypically untidy follow-up. Short and wide down leg side
wide of off stump, but this time Hayden gets a bat to it in a mistimed drive
a double-whirl of the arms, one of Flintoff's little tricks, and a good ball too. TIghter and fuller, and defended late
forward and pushed down the ground again
shorter and outside off stump, steered off the back foot to gully. Only 82mph so far (132kph) which is short of his usual pace
a push-and-go to mid-off. Easy run, but perhaps it shouldn't have been. Symonds, for instance, would have turned that into a run-out chance
more width for the batsman, but point does well to intercept a slapped steer
leg-side, poor bowling
short and nudged off the hip into space on the leg-side
Plunkett's bowling on both sides of the wicket at the moment, and this time he strays onto Ponting's pads - never a good plan. Gets away with it though, as fine leg tidies up
fuller and straighter. The pitch isn't quite as fast as it might be though, and Ponting can't time his drive
ping! Right in the slot for Ponting, who swings lustily across the line and deposits an off-stump delivery over long-on!
great pounce from Panesar at deep mid-off, cuts off a certain boundary from a firm drive
drawn forward in a defensive push.
slower ball, but that emerges as a horrid loopy full-toss. Hayden latches on immediately and thumps that down the ground!
wide half-volley, but Hayden times it too well and drives to extra cover. A let-off
straighter and turned into the leg-side
pushed into the covers and a quick call for a single. Joyce fields well and shies, just misses at the non-striker's end. Could have been tight!
pushed into the covers to complete a reasonable over for England, runs-wise
tidy start, floated onto a good length and pushed into the covers
trading singles, as Hayden steps back and clips a gentle tweaker into the leg-side
forward in a measured drive. One more to deep extra cover
another clip through midwicket. Singles, singles, everywhere
one more, one more. Nothing much wrong from Panesar, but he's hampered by his field restrictions. This one was a bit shorter and wider though
quicker delivery on leg-stump, Hayden closes the face, and that's seven effortless runs off a pretty blameless over
Full and defended. Nixon standing up to add to the pressure
Ponting back and angles the ball to the left of backward point
sweetly timed clip off his legs through midwicket
Ponting opens up and thumps the ball to Strauss at deep extra cover
Hayden taps the ball into the off and thinks about a single by Joyce is in quickly at short extra cover

same shot by this time placed wide of Joyce and a yell of "two, two" as soon as he hit it. The man in the deep had a long way to come in, so while the ball barely left the fielding circle it was easy to come back for the second
one step, pushed firmly to mid-on, too firmly to allow the single
placed into the gap in the covers for another ambled single
wide, no spin, and pushed into space in the covers
full, again hit against the spin up to mid-on
Ponting slips into the covers, no run and Hayden had to turn smartly as he had come some way down the track by the time Ponting called "no"
driven to mid-on, Joyce sprinting in from short midwicket put them off the run even thought he ended up diving over the ball
driven firmly back at - and past - Collingwood and fielded at long-on
Ponting back and punches the ball into the off side
firm straight drive, Collingwood just misses touching the ball which hammers into the stumps with Hayden a long way out of his crease. Ponting then races down the pitch before being sent back himself
thumped into the covers where Strauss makes a good stop at extra cover
pushed up the ground to long-on
clipped into the leg side for an easy one to end the over
pushed into the leg side but not into space
driven back to the bowler with no real pace
steered into the off side, again he finds the fielder at point
whipped behind square on the leg side to bring up his 29th one-day fifty
pushed into the off for a well-judged single, good communication
worked into the leg side
Hayden shapes to run the ball down to third man, misses by a whisker and throws his head back in frustration
firmly pushed to long-on
weak drive to extra cover
full, Ponting waited and placed that just out of the grasp of a diving extra cover
driven again, but not timed as sweetly and it bobbles up to extra cover
wristy whip through midwicket
into space between cover and extra cover
Ponting takes a big stride and drives the ball up and over Panesar for a two-bounce four
tickled behind square on the leg
forward and blocked
pushed up to long-off for an ambled single
textbook cover drive but not timed
speared down the leg side and a bemused-looking Nixon parries rather than stops
better line, blocked
Hayden takes a big stride, drives and well stopped at short cover
leading edge to a flick/drive and it almost carries back to a sprawling Dalrymple
again straight to short cover
a bit of a heave/sweep, hitting across the line and a loud but rather overambitious shout for leg-before
clipped into the leg side and deep midwicket has to hare in to prevent the second
driven to deep cover
short and wide, flat batted by Ponting to deepish mid-off
full, driven to mid-off and as both batsmen set off as soon as it is hit, always a run. Mid-on is back on the 30-yard line
opens the face and steers into the packed off side
Ponting takes a step but the ball is speared in at his feet and he can do no more than pat it back
checked drive across the line and it loops a few yards short of Strauss who was charging in from deep midwicket
slower ball, leg side, and clipped fine where Panesar has to scuttle round from wide long leg
driven firmly to the left of mid-off where Flintoff has to slide on his knees to gather
fullish and crisply thumped straightishly to long-off
Ponting turned square as he shapes to whip it through the leg side  and the ball ends up squirting to extra cover
into the off side which is heavily fortified
another slower ball, Ponting pushes it back, Mahmood shapes to throw it back at the striker's end which would have been fine had he not completely missed picking it up
sprayed wildly down the off side
wide half-volley, Hayden frees his arms and thumps it over extra cover, not timed as well as it could have been but it still had enough gas to reach the rope
pushed back to Flintoff
super shot, full and Hayden smashes it over midwicket where it bounces a yard inside the rope. That time he did middle it
push and run to extra cover to bring up the hundred partnership off 115 deliveries
Ponting drops it into the off side, no more than five yards from the crease, and comes through for one to bring up his 58th ODI fifty ... the 80th time he has passed the landmark in all
pushed into the off side but this time to a man
slower ball, not timed into the off side
ye another slower ball. Ponting waits and cracks it past extra cover
short, swatted dismissively over midwicket, sweetly timed
plopped into the covers but a quick shout of "no" as the fielders converge
a rather ugly heave through midwicket from well outside off stump, but it was short enough for him to try that even thought he didn't really get hold of it
more vim there - 89mph (143kph) which thuds into Hayden's midriff as he tries to pull it
too leg side, clipped to deep midwicket
pushed into the covers for a well-run single
full, cracked back straight but to a fielder
full, squeezed out but again right at cover
pushed into the covers for a well-run single
leg-side, clipped to deep midwicket
pushed out to deep cover
dragged down the leg-side, Hayden responds with quick feet but can't get it away
big carve over point. Plugs into the deep, and nearly a run-out as they hesitate over the second. Unusually ponderous running from this pair
Hayden comes forward and then steps back, Dalrymple isn't fooled and in the end Hayden settles for one as he steers the ball behind square on the off
more tip and run. Dalrymple has bowled well but still conceded a run-a-ball
driven back at the bowler who collapses in a heap to stop it
placed into the covers
Hayden goes back to a slightly short one and paddles it to long-on
Ponting takes two big strides and makes the delivery into a half volley, thumping it over mid-on
no run into the off side

oh dear. pushed into the covers, Hayden committed to the run is stranded, Dalrymple underarms to Panesar who makes a complete mess of it, demolishing the stumps as he tries to collect the ball and there are overthrows to add insult to injury. The throw wasn't great but even so ...
pushed to leg for a single
a single into the leg side
angled behind square on the off
nothing shot, into the covers, no run
Ponting opens his arms and smashes that past extra cover
Hayden back and flicks that just behind square on the leg
Ponting drives rather uppishly over extra covers, tag fielding in the deep which all goes rather wrong and to the jeers of the crowd they run an extra one

What a catch! Brilliant pluck from Collingwood at short cover - that was a bit of a filthy long-hop from Panesar, to be honest, but Ponting rocked back and clobbered it - it was in the air for too long and Collingwood dived back and across to his left, and clung onto a one-handed screamer!
good line and length to start, and a measured push to get off the mark
width for Hayden, and driven out to point
solid delivery, nice flight and loop, watchful defence from the new batsman
bat and pad firmly together as this one is defended as well
excellent ball-on-a-string stuff from Panesar. Tidy and successful over
clipped into the leg-side
bit of tweak from a good length, played out to square leg
squared up a fraction, but clipped fine
nudged into the off side for a quick single
quicker ball, and wide outside off stump
driven down the ground
bowling, Monty, bowling
fraction shorter, and nudged down to third man
driven up to mid-on
pushed into the leg-side, and they hustle through for another quick single. Had to scamper as mid-on was swooping
wild slog, ugly slog. That was a quicker ball from Panesar, and nearly fizzed through to off stump
tip and run again to midwicket. If he'd hit he was out, but the throw was wild
floated onto middle-and-leg, clipped firmly to midwicket's left. Another single

big, big, swing, and that's an excellent catch from Mahmood on the long-on boundary! Hayden went for the big yahoo, looked to have hit it clean out of the ground but got fractionally underneath it. The ball topped out somewhere near floodlight height, but Mahmood kept his cool, and acknowledged his inevitable barrackers in the crowd
drawn forward in defence
tight, tight run, and that's gone to the third umpire ... but the replays are inconclusive. It was punched to midwicket where Collingwood threw, but Nixon couldn't quite get the bails off in time
sharp spin, inside edge onto the pads
driven firmly back at the bowler, parried to mid-off
back of a length and turned to midwicket
bit of width and carved straight to point
width again, and this time the gap is picked
cut to deep backward point
hoisted over extra-cover for a big six! Lovely strike

Panesar has his second! Hodge was down on the sweep, and umpire Harper upholds a massive appeal! That was not a clever decision, to be honest. Hodge was a long way down, and it was way outside the line of off stump. Apart from that, pretty good
pushed out to cover to get off the mark immediately
sharp turn from middle-and-leg. Pushed out to point
turning again into the pads, clipped to midwicket
down on one knee, and that's threaded elegantly through the covers. Bit too much width
outside leg, swept fine and hard, and that's Hussey's first boundary
good flight and direction. Pushed back up the track
full-toss, but Hussey doesn't make best use of it. All the same, it's two more out to deep midwicket, and nine off the over
drawn forward and pushed firmly past a floundering mid-on
a bit of width, and Joyce at backward point is down quickly to cut off two runs. Good fielding
tip and run into the leg side. Half an appeal from Panesar, and that was probably closer than his lbw!
opened the face of the bat, steered past gully
opened the face of the bat, steered past gully
flashed into the covers
fiddled into the leg-side for another quick single
forward in a measured drive, another single
turned to square leg and as the batsmen saw it was Panesar they took the second
soft hands into the off side
smacked an attempted drive into his feet and a well-=run single. Always hard to stop them taking one for that
short outside off stump, mistimed paddle and stopped by a sprawling short cover
again a decent tumbling stop by Bell at short cover
a controlled edge to third man
checked defensive shot, almost played on the run, and a scurried single
Hussey hurried by that one and he can do no more than push the ball to Dalrymple at short midwicket
slower ball to start with - or perhaps he is just stiff - and it's turned to long-on
driven, slightly uppishly, between cover and extra cover
dropped Hussey takes a big stride and drives in the air to Mahmood at mid-on ...he sunk to his knees and waited for it ... and then it bounced off his wrists ... poor drop
flicked off the back foot to midwicket
driven to long-on
Clarke turns it behind square where Panesar makes a tumblings top to a few cheers
checked block into the off side, fielders in like bees to a honeypot

slower ball, played into the off side, Collingwood swoops and throws down the stumps at the non-striker's end. Clarke must have assumed he was safe as he didn't stretch and replays show that he was a couple of inches short. A big cheer as the third umpire's verdict is shown
two in two! just short of a length, Hussey shapes to run the ball to third man but it's too close to him and he gets a thin nick to Nixon. Hussey doesn't even wait for the decision ...
short and wide, slashed in the air between and slightly over men at point and gully. Flintoff gives a wry smile
prodded to point with a loud shout of "wait, wait, wait"
similar ball to the one that got Hussey, Hogg aims a big wipe and misses
Watson back and plays into the leg side. Uncertainty between the two over the run
Watson back and pushes square into the off side
down the leg side, Hogg shimmies inside the line and then looks worriedly at the umpire in case he wasn't going to call it
pushed square on the off side and Collingwood in quickly and had he hit at the bowler's end then Hogg wouldn't have even been in the frame
into the off side, a more comfortable single this time
ugly reach into the leg side, but effective
firm on-drive to the man in the deep
checked drive to short midwicket
same again but this time it just evades the dive by Bell
slightly overpitched and driven wide of the man in saving the one and on to long-off
slower ball, spotted, and turned to square leg
driven to deep cover
good delivery which Watson gently plays back to Flintoff
Hogg turned square and the ball squirts out to gully
full and a wristy flick down to long leg off middle-and-leg stump
Watson steps to leg and cracks it through extra cover, Strauss in the deep makes good ground to field
Watson again steps to leg, Plunkett sees it and follows him, and Watson can only steer the ball to point
driven to deepish extra cover
Hogg steps back, completely mistimes a cut and hammers the ball into the ground at his feet ... but it still produces a run as Watson quick to call him through
Hogg steps back and thumps it straight to Bell at extra cover. He timed it but right into the fielder's midriff
Lee rather jumpily back as he jabs down on the ball
Lee aims an expansive swish through the covers, gets a thick inside edge and Nixon makes a good stop diving to his left
mistimed drive, Dalrymple dives full length from extra cover to keep Lee on strike
frustration showing as Lee tries to swipe the ball over midwicket and misses

Collingwood is on fire! Lee, clearly frustrated, swished and missed, the ball cannoned off his pads to Collingwood at backward point and his underarm throw hit the stumps with Lee, diving full length, a yard short
clipped to midwicket for an easy - and almost gifted -  single
slower ball, inside edge to midwicket and after a moment's yes-noing, they decide to stay put
angled poke to backward point and they risk - and get - a single to Collingwood

another one bites the dust ... Watson is undone by a slower ball which he lamely chips to Bell at midwicket. Watson's ignominy was compounded by the fact he then headed off towards the wrong exit and had to make a sudden and big navigational correction when he realised his mistake. The crowd spotted it and gave him a few jeers ...
prodded into the off side
defensive push beats the bowler and extra cover and Bracken trots through to keep the strike
edged fine to third man
full toss, patted to mid-off. He is looking for the yorker ...
full and straight and McGrath's 37th birthday present from Flintoff is to have his stumps scattered

inn2.comm: full, fast, inswinging, nice start for Lee. Joyce defends cagily to point
off the mark, slightly too straight and nudged off the hip
forward and pushing firmly into the covers
there's that troublesome area for Loye. A bit of width, and he does well not to throw the bat at it
width again, but too wide this time to be at all tempted. Not called as such though
solid start for both Lee and Loye. Full and fast again, and a well-timed defensive stroke is picked up in the covers
good start for the left-armer, a curve-ball outside off stump and Joyce leaves alone
more swing towards the slips, but Joyce plays defiantly straight, well inside the line of the ball
fuller and tighter to off stump. Joyce is half-forward in defence and edges that into the leg side
a big appeal, but that was sneaking down leg. No swing that time, which took it straight on, and maybe a hint of inside-edge too. Good bowling
Joyce, caught in two minds, has a dart at this one, another outswinger. Bracken is mixing it up well
lovely over. This one is fuller again, and defended into the gully. A maiden, and a tidy one. Rather like Lara Bingle, if I may say so
outside off again. Lee is determined to exploit Loye's weakness to the wide one. But Loye resists temptation this time

The slower ball does the trick! This one was fuller, and Loye was deceived as he shuffled across his stumps. A huge appeal is upheld by umpire Harper, but Hawkeye reckons that was sliding down leg ...
forward, and defended into the leg side
width this time to the left-hander, but Joyce can't time a wafty drive. Cover fields
full-length on off stump, again some useful outswing probing the edge of the bat
a bit of a slap outside off, and that bounces just short of point to complete a successful over
confident, attacking, frame of mind for Bell. Advancing down the pitch to ease Bracken through the covers
more attacking intent, but this time forced back by a slight shortening of length. Nice bowling
big stride again, but defended in the end. Bell is looking to be dominant
slower ball, and Bell is off the strike with a checked steer through gully
good running - a gentle nurdle into the leg side, and off for the single straightaway

thwack! That's the shot Bell's been looking for! Advancing down the pitch once again, Bracken drops short, Bell rocks back and pulls handsomely through midwicket. Promising response to their early set-back
good length and defended
lovely strike, this time from Joyce. Too much width from Lee, but that was sweetly timed with a flick of the wrists through point.
watchful this time. Playing inside the line and left alone
excellent channel from Lee. Full, fast, hint of outswing, tight to off stump. A good leave from Joyce
once again, left alone because of the late swing. That was fractionally wider

GONE! That was a horrible misjudgment from Joyce - tried to work a straighter delivery over midwicket, but instead chipped tamely to Glenn McGrath, who had to stoop forward as the ball plopped into his palms
slightly wide of off stump, steered into the covers
wide again, and edged safely down to third man to bring Strauss onto strike
good tight line, Strauss is forced back onto his stumps to defend

another one gone! This is getting rather chaotic for England now. A nothing sort of shot from Strauss, he shuffled across his stumps, tried to work to leg, and was trapped plumb in front. All too easy for Australia at the moment
angled across the right hander, left well alone
tighter to off stump this time, and defended. Another successful over for Australia
yorker length, but a slower ball - 80mph (128.8kph). Defended easily
nippier this time. Back up towards 90mph (144.5kph). Defended with a hop off the back foot
fuller and faster still (92.2mph, 148kph). Lee fields in his followthrough and shapes to shy at the stumps
hint of width, but Bell has been forced back, and can't find the gap
good shot for no runs, a firm clip off the legs, but Brad Hodge fields well at midwicket
edged! But all along the ground, and all the way to the boundary! Bell played that with soft hands, which was the key
zippy and just back of a length. Collingwood steps back into his crease to steer into the covers
wider, and that's a wild swing and a miss. Exasperation all round, not least from the batsman
slightly straighter. Collingwood has a swish again, and inside-edges onto his thigh
back and across very early, but it's a slower ball so plenty of time to defend it to leg
forward in a solid defensive prod
smacked! That was stand-and-deliver stuff from Collingwood. Another slower ball, picked it early, and thwacked it high over mid-on! Good batting
short, Bell defends off the back foot, the ball drops into the crease and Collingwood races through for a good quick single
fended into the covers off the front foot
shorter, and Bell hops into line to turn this round the corner. Hodge fields on the slide at backward square
aimed at the blockhole, angled in. Driven well, but straight to mid-on
92.8mph (149.5kph) and aimed at the pads. Turned straight to the man on the 45
back and across, and defended into the gully
a bit of luck for Collingwood as he inside-edges a defensive shot into the leg-side, and Bell hustles him through as Gilchrist runs round to field
tidy clip through midwicket. Speared into the pads
pushed out to cover, but he was neither forward nor back, so no great power
opens the face, steers to point
pushed to mid-off with soft hands. More good running
pushed out to point to complete another good over
full and fast again, defended into the leg side
appreciable inswing, but started on middle so easily flicked to fine leg
width, but at 91.6mph (147kph) it proves a little too hard to wallop. Bell misses out
fuller and faster. Dug out in a hurry to great yelps from the field
angled into the pads again, but too quick to clip away. Fielded by Lee in his followthrough
speared down the leg side for the first extra of the innings
another attempt to flick round the corner, but easily picked up by short fine leg
outside off stump, attempted steer into the leg side, but muffed
wider this time. Pushed into the covers
wider and slashed over the top to third man
dropped! And it's the birthday boy, Glenn McGrath, who grasses a sitter at square leg! Bell went for a big heave over the top, and the ball burst straight through his hands and onto his chin!
poked out to point
defended into the gully, and that's the end of an over that promises more
a tidy enough first delivery though. Perfect line, perfect length, softly paddled down the pitch
good areas Glenn. Defended with a bobble
slightly shorter and arrow-straight. Played with soft hands into the gully for another quick single
shorter and Bell sizes up a paddle-pull through midwicket. But instead he takes one in the midriff
fuller - attempted yorker but a fraction off line. Pushed into the covers with no alarms
straight through him! Bell tried to whip that through midwicket but was lucky not to get an edge to the keeper as he did so.
good start. Right on the money, and defended
good shape back into the batsman. Collingwood drops the ball at his feet
tight, probing stuff. Just on or about off stump, and pushed back up the pitch
slower ball, slightly wider but no real room for manoeuvre. Played out to point
just back of a length, eased down the ground for a gentle single
very tidy first over. Just there or thereabouts throughout. A lull in proceedings for the moment, as England attempt to regroup
a bit of width, and Collingwood misses with an attempted dab to third man
a fraction wider on the crease, Collingwood uses the angle to clip to leg
opens the face and steers to third man
quick single as Collingwood walks across his stumps and misses an attempted clip
squirted down to third man again. England content to trade in singles
back in that corridor of uncertainty. Defended
worked to fine leg, picks his gap well
bouncer, and an effective one. Bell bails out of his attempted pull, and that's the one for the over signalled
another single as this one is pushed up to mid-on. This is good running between the wickets
nurdled again, this time through square leg with a shuffle across the crease
slower ball, well directed, well up to the bat, and pushed out to mid-on
good finish to the over. Wider on the crease, and defended into the leg side
good length delivery on the off stump. Solidly into line
turned to midwicket
the ever-green Glenn McGrath chips in with another fine wicket-to-wicket delivery
a touch more width, and this one is dabbed down to third man
fuller length on the legs, clipped away
lovely ball, right in that off-stump channel. An attempted nurdle nearly takes the edge!
back of a length on middle-and-leg, turned to square leg
up and under! Great strike, lofted high over the infield and down to the long-off boundary
clipped fine. Another single
attempts to work into the leg side. Misses. But they get a run anyway
on the legs again, but singles are all England are after for the moment
back on off stump, pushed out to point. Steady accumulation from England
right up to the bat on off stump, good finish to the over
flicked high over backward square leg. A bit of a top-edge, but safe enough
a bit short from McGrath and that's forcefully worked into the leg side, but tidied up in the deep
fuller and swinging onto the pads, a firm clip again
good line, good length, defended with respect
down the track and shovelled into the leg-side. A little cramped on the shot as McGrath adjusted late, but got good bat on it to work it in front of square
looking to advance again, and pushed down to mid-off
steps across and works to leg
excellent lofted strike - that's Collingwood's slot, and the ball pings high over midwicket for a one-bounce four!
tighter to the stumps, and worked to leg

outside leg stump, and that's a horrid misfield from that birthday boy again. The ball just dribbled through his legs at backward square, and he was left on all fours like a rather disconsolate giraffe
another quick single, but that would have been out if Ponting's throw from mid-on had hit the stumps.
misdirected and flicked to fine leg. Valuable runs!
another nurdlbd single, and that's a good over from England, as their runs worm begin to turn upwards
pushed to mid-off for another jogged single
short, wide and slapped over point. England are picking up the tempo
tighter line, turned back down the pitch
much better line and length. Nothing but a respectful push into the covers
walloped! Collingwood came down the track and got right underneath that, just enough legs to clear the ropes right behind the bowler's head!
fuller, probably faster and speared in at a yorker length, but Collingwood picks it early and clips through leg. Good over again for England
nipbacker, whipped fine
bouncer, doesn't get up much, but effective enough
turned to leg again. The runs keep ticking over
short, and swung into the deep. Not much menace in the Australian attack at present. Maybe time for a bit of spin to change things?
fuller length, driven firmly to mid-on, but too firmly to get any runs out of it
too short to be a fraction off line, as that ball was. Clipped fine again
looped onto a good length, and swept square
big full toss, but Bell was already committed to a sweep, so rather robbed himself there
poor ball, down the leg side, and Hogg curses himself
back on a better line, delicately worked into the leg side
tossed up outside off to bring up the 100
nurdle, nurdle. England keep picking the gaps and working the singles
fuller, floated onto a length. Firmly driven straight back to the bowler to end the over
twirled onto a decent length first up
oops, that slipped. Another extra to the total
better line
down on the sweep, and paddled fine
good rotation of the strike. No alarms for England at the moment
tossed up, and swept again
slightly shorter, and punched into the gap. Ponting has a furrowed brow
looped up and Bell is drawn into the drive. Just misses the edge
prodded out to point, and that's a very important half-century for Paul Collingwood. His 13th in ODIs, and following straight on from his hundred last week
Bell returns the strike with another deft dab
singles, singles everywhere. Australia are in need of inspiration. This one is steered to gully
full face of the bat this time
glanced to backward square. Another nurdlesome over
deflected past Gilchrist's gloves. Can't really call that a chance. It was played so late
"sloppy" announces Nasser Hussain. And he's not wrong
back on a better length
clipped out to leg again
another single and that's the hundred stand from a very respectable 122 balls
stroked down to long-on. And England press onwards
that's a bit of a rank wide, to be frank. Way outside off
better line and length, a bit of a leading edge but not much of a threat
tossed up outside off again
down the track and played back to the bowler
missed sweep
and that one is cut to backward point. Mixing things up nicely after that initial wide.
driven to cover
big full toss swept out to deep backward squad, fine fifty for Bell off 72 balls
slotted straight to cover
flicked into the gap at midwicket
swept fine as this pair continue to rotate the strike
another of England's favourite shot, the sweep, and another useful over for the team
hits the off stump line first up and Collingwood moves back and across to play from the crease
worked backward of square
nicely deflected down to third man
hit into the pad, drops by Collingwood's feet and they scamper a sharp single. Ah, here we go, McGrath's first moan of the spell...asking if Collingwood actually played a shot at that!
turned to midwicket, but can't find the gap
drifting onto leg stump, turned down to fine leg and another fumble allows them back for two. The Aussies not at their best in the field today
walks across his crease, turned into the leg side and another overthrow conceded
pushed to cover point for a single
edged into the gully area, they sprint through
worked out to deep square-leg, milking the bowling with ease at the moment
and the deep square-leg man is in action again as Bell moves across the crease and works it away
An 87mph (140kph) loosener from Lee and defended into the covers
guided down to third man, using Lee's pace
pushed into the covers, can't find the gap
quick from Lee, 90.5mph (145kph), and an inside edge thuds into the pads and rolls out into the off side
well bowled, hint of movement into Bell who rides it well and turns to the leg side
bouncer, Collingwood sways underneath. Testing comeback over from Lee, he's Australia's main weapon today
well outside off stump, but still tries to sweep. Why not drive it down to long off?
back into his crease and worked to vacant square-leg area
comes down the track, makes it into a full toss, chipped down the ground and falls short of long on
leading edge this time, loops over cover and long off is on his heels allowing two. More teapots from the Australians
pushed into the covers
short, quicker, Collingwood latches onto it but not quite with enough power to reach the fence
pulled out through square leg and this time it's Hayden who makes a mess of it and another couple to the total. Poor stuff from the Aussies, sorry it's been a long winter just had to squeeze that in!
behind it, into the off side
firmly driven to mid off, England notice it's McGrath there and scamper for a single. That's called picking your fielder
slightly cramped for room, pushed into the covers
rides the bounce, falls by his feet, they set off and Lee charges through but can't flick the ball onto the stumps
there it is! huge breakthrough for Australia. Pinpoint yorker from Lee and Bell can't get his bat down in time. Hint of reverse swing and missed it by the width of his bat
worked through square leg
comes forward, thick inside edge dribbles way to short fine-leg
worked back to the bowler, diving save from Hogg
pushed out to the man on the square-leg fence
Flintoff didn't pick that, plays an ugly shot into the covers off the back foot
slammed to the man at cover
starts with a bumper, ducks out of the way

wow, it's all happening. Collingwood pulls through square leg, throw goes to Gilchrist's end who throws it to Lee at the bowler's end who drops the ball and breaks the stumps with his hand...Flintoff might just have made it but another mistake from Australia. Also, if Gilchrist had broken his stumps, Collingwood was well out
thick inside edge into the leg side, falls just short of Ponting at short midwicket
pushed out to point
clubbed in the air down to long on, falls short of the man on the fence, not middled by Flintoff
along the deck this time, down the ground to keep the strike
cut out to point
finds the gap at cover this time, out to the sweeper
gee, Flintoff really can't read the wrist spin. Tries to work through the leg side and almost a leading edge back to Hogg
dropped! another leading edge from Flintoff out to cover, Mitchell Johnson is on as sub and makes a great dive but can't hold on at full stretch. What a let-off
tries to guide through point, finds the fielder
well run, dropped into the off side and they both set off straight away
defends, ball bounces down by his feet, Flintoff kicks it away to make sure it doesn't hit the stumps...almost thought of a single, you can't do that!
charges and top-edges down to third man
think inside edge, into the pad and back to McGrath
punched down to long on
hint of reverse swing, full and into Flintoff's toes and can't get it further than midwicket. Good over from McGrath, but he's got some catching up to do
full and outside off stump, driven to the cover sweeper
bosh! that breaks the shackles somewhat, Flintoff launches this over wide long on for a maximum. That's his best shot so far by some way
short this time, pulled through square leg and that makes eight off two balls
pushed into the covers
out to the man on the cover fence
close! edged just wide of slip but that's a great over for England...brings the asking rate down
pushed forward and gets a thick outside edge which flies close to the man at backward point and down to third man
worked to midwicket, well fielded nothing there
tries to angle it into the off side, but just finds point
short, rocks back and pulls over midwicket with enough placement to get a brace, plenty of space on the MCG outfield
slower ball chipped over midwicket, just out of his reach and away to the deep midwicket fence for a precious boundary
pushed down to long off
short and hammered away but straight to deep midwicket
down on one knee, connects well with a sweep and places it for a couple out to deep square leg
very full, forced down to long off
oops, very odd. Collingwood tries to paddle this round the corner, gets a top edge over Gilchrist's head and goes away behind the keeper
full, can't force it away
tries to give himself room to cut, misses and Gilchrist takes
full-length, right up in the blockhole, dug out back to the bowler
driven down the ground, excellent running brings two just as the throw comes in from the cover boundary
worked into the leg side, another one notched off
speared in on off stump. Defended with no great foot movement to point. Another single though ...
quick feet, and Collingwood is already running as this one is chipped up to long-on. Ponting looks like thunder
shorter and a bit of width, but Flintoff picks out point to complete the over.
looped onto a length, defended back up the track
too wide, and that's carved out to the covers, and they jog another single
a big swish and a miss! But Flintoff's back foot is firmly anchored as the bails come off
on the spot and respectfully played
dancing feet from Flintoff, and a smear across the line brings another run. Inelegant but effective
sharp tweak, and a bit of an appeal, but always sliding down leg
90mph first up (144kph) and deflected down to third man. That's the fifty stand
went for the yorker, Flintoff went for the swish, and that's a thick inside-edge, squirted down to fine leg. Another single ...
another inswinging yorker, squirted out to point this time. Collingwood calls the single to regain the strike
slower ball, but misdirected. Ironically, Australia might not mind him having another ball in this over ...
quicker but down the leg side again! That's less good from Lee, and Gilchrist grimaces.
crikey! Another yorker, Collingwood jabbed down late, Flintoff and Lee were in a desperate race for the line, and that is mighty, mighty tight! But not out! Flintoff's dive just beat Lee's underarm
banged in, but the new ball doesn't get up much and whistles harmlessly by. A precious dot ball though ...
94mph yorker (151kph), but misdirected, and Flintoff clips a single to keep the strike
down the track to meet the new bowler, picks the gap on the off-side with a measured drive
slower-ball bouncer. A bit wide but Collingwood was fooled nonetheless
a firm clump off the back foot into space in the covers. Short cover dives despairingly but can't cut it off
full length, and Flintoff gives himself a bit of room to place that firmly into the deep, wide of long-off. Picked up on the slide, but two more to the total
Flintoff feigns a retreat to leg, Watson bangs it in and another two, a firm cut into the deep.
the crowd get excited as Watson leaps to cling onto a return drive, but it's a bump-ball
fantastic ball! Speared right up in the blockhole, inswinging and ideal length. But Collingwood gets good bat on it and that's another one to the total
more frustration for Lee! Flintoff makes room and digs out another yorker with a big swing. Inside-edge to square-leg
shorter this time, and Flintoff has a big mow over midwicket. Decent strike brings one more

top-edge loops ... safe! Lands in no-man's land at square leg, and that is Collingwood's second hundred in consecutive games, and his fourth in ODIs! Brilliant, brilliant innings, and England are inching ever closer
short, and shovelled into the leg side
full-length again, well dug out for another quick single ... and a no-ball!
clubbed confidently down the ground, and Lee has been seen off. A valiant spell, but is it in vain on this occasion?
outside off, on a good length, but another confident swing of the bat sends the ball down to long-off

short, Flintoff swishes, and that's gone! It was a bit flat-footed from Flintoff, and a very, very thin graze through to Gilchrist! Watson has made the breakthrough! The end of an excellent 74-run stand, and is this a late glimmer for Australia?
width from Watson, but that's an air-shot first-up. It's a tough time to come to the middle ...
excellent line and length, Dalrymple gets good bat on it, but straight to point
played out to point, hesitation in the run and Clarke's shy hits the stumps at the non-striker's end! Dalrymple is home though, and that's overthrows as well!
played with soft hands into the covers, another sharp single completes an eventful over

McGrath's made the difference! Inswinging low full-toss, an excellent ball in the circumstances, squirted out to point, and Clark's return to the bowler is pinpoint! Dalrymple was late setting off and was never in the frame ...
brilliant fielding by Ponting at mid-on! Dived full-stretch to cut off the run!
bit of width, pushed into the covers, that's another single ...
a risk-free single nudged down to long-on
wide outside off stump, pushed confidently back past the bowler, and tidied up at long-off
massive shout! But McGrath is coming around the wicket, and umpire Harper believes that's sliding down. Hawkeye doesn't agree! Lucky break for Nixon who shuffled right across his stumps
full-toss, and that's a vital boundary for England! Collingwood down on the sweep, picks his spot perfectly just behind square, and Brad Hodge's despairing dive can't cut it off!
two fours in two balls, and that was an even better shot! Slower ball from Watson, and Collingwood scooped that up and over McGrath at fine leg!
wider line, and Collingwood picks the gap in the covers. England need almost a run a ball
excellent cricket from Nixon. On off stump, tip and run into the off side. Collingwood back on strike ...
would have been out if it had hit! Collingwood looked for the sweep, played to mid-on instead and Nixon was late setting off. The shy missed by a whisker!
slower ball, clubbed down the ground, through long-off! 13 from 12 ...
full-length, whipped through the leg side, England run two to fine leg, and it's 11 off 11!
Nixon charges, McGrath intercepts a checked drive above his head, the crowd think it's a catch, but in fact it's a dot ball!
great cricket from Nixon. Big gaps on the leg side, and he worked it expertly off his toes into the gap. England need a run a ball again ...
low full-toss, clipped to the mid-off fielder in the ring, but another quick single ...
drilled down the ground! That's a massive strike! Great quick feet from Collingwood, and McGrath couldn't cut it off!
full-toss, back to McGrath. A single threatened, but wisely turned down
full-length from around the wicket, Nixon whips it fine again, and he's found space as well!
tip and run and the scores are level! Chipped to mid-on and Nixon is too quick for the fielder
There it is! And it's Paul Collingwood with the winning runs through midwicket!
